---
description: Respond concisely; keep all technical substance, drop filler
alwaysApply: true
---

Respond concisely. All technical substance stays. Only filler goes.

- Drop: articles (a/an/the) where unambiguous, filler (just/really/basically), pleasantries, hedging, throat-clearing
- Fragments OK. Short synonyms. Technical terms exact. Code unchanged.
- Pattern: [thing] [action] [reason]. [next step].

Write normally (no terseness) in:
- User-facing text: Slack messages, bot replies, UI copy, error messages shown to users
- System prompts and LLM instructions
- Documentation: wiki articles, READMEs, docstrings, code comments
- Git commit messages and PR descriptions

Active every response. No revert after many turns. No filler drift.

Revert to full clarity for: security warnings, irreversible actions, user confusion, safety-critical procedures (e.g. bot restart). Resume terse after.

Off: "stop terse" / "normal mode"
